Put the @porcini mushrooms{15%g}, @chicken stock pot{1} and @water{750%ml} in a 
large #saucepan{} on medium heat. Bring to a simmer to release the flavour 
of the mushrooms and stir to dissolve the stock pot. Halve, peel and chop the 
@echalion shallot{1} into ½cm pieces. Peel and grate the @garlic clove{1} 
(or use a #garlic press{}). Thinly slice the @chestnut mushrooms{1}. Roughly 
chop the @flat leaf parsley{1}(roughly chopped, stalks and all). Zest the 
@lemon{½}(zested).

Preheat your #oven{} to 200°C. Lay two slices of @serrano ham{1} lengthways 
and slightly overlapping on a #chopping board{}. Place the 
@British chicken breasts{2} horizontally across the middle of the ham. Wrap 
the ham around the chicken to enclose it. Place them seam-side down on a 
#baking tray{}. Repeat with the remaining chicken and ham. Roast the 
chicken on the top shelf of your oven for ~{20-22%minutes}.

Meanwhile, put a glug of @olive oil{2%tbsp} in a large, #wide-bottomed saucepan{}
on medium heat. Add the shallot and mushrooms. Cook, stirring, until the 
shallot is soft, ~{5-6%minutes}. Add the garlic and cook for ~{1%minute} more. 
Pour in the @risotto rice{175%g} and stir. Cook for ~{1%minute} so the rice 
gets a good coating of the flavours in the pan. Add a ladle of the stock and 
stir. Once the rice has absorbed the stock, add another ladleful and repeat.

Continue adding ladlefuls of stock, stirring regularly until it has all been 
absorbed by the rice. This should take ~{20-25%minutes}. Don't leave the 
porcini mushrooms behind - make sure you add them too!

> TIP: Let the rice absorb each ladleful of stock before adding the next.

In between stints of stirring, put olive oil in a #small bowl{} and add the 
lemon zest and parsley.

When the chicken is cooked through remove from your oven and leave to rest on 
the baking tray, covered in #foil{} to keep warm.

> TIP: The chicken is cooked when it is no longer pink in the middle.

When the risotto is ready, add the @unsalted butter{15%g} and 
@grated hard Italian style cheese{40%g} and stir vigorously. Taste the 
risotto for seasoning and add more @salt{} and @black pepper{} if you like.

Cut each chicken breast into six slices. Spoon the risotto into deep 
#bowls{} and top with the @wild rocket{1}. Sit the chicken on top of the 
rocket and finish with a drizzle of the lemon and parsley oil. Buon appetito!